    "updated_at": "2016-05-16T23:39:54Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz It appears this issue should not have been closed (?) - at least, I can't get control of the tray context menu in the way described by @jasisk. Was it classified as a \"won't fix\", or perhaps is there a way to achieve this result that I'm not getting? The exact behavior I'd like to set up is:  \n- left click: `show()` the main window.\n- right click: open the context menu.\n\nI can get this behavior on windows (which normally uses the right click for the context menu) but not on mac. On mac, the context menu pops up on left click regardless, and click events do not seem to trigger at all.\n"
